This file contains information about how the Gibbs free energies of formation of
the species are calculated.

General algorithm:

    1) Determine or find minimal energy structure of the species.

    2) These are used as input for a vibrational analysis with
    Gaussian 09, Revision E.01 Frisch et al. 2013
    (http://gaussian.com/g09citation/)

    3) The output (rotational, vibrational, ... energies)
    are used to compute the Gibbs free energy of formation at 1e5 Pa
    (as used by JANAF tables http://kinetics.nist.gov/janaf/), according
    to the algorithm on the documentation pages of the thermochemical part of
    GaussianO9 (http://gaussian.com/thermo/).
    The needed atomic properties (enthaly of formation, difference of enthalpy
    w.r.t. a reference temperature, and the total enthropy) were taken from
    JANAF tables. The potential energy of the constituent atoms was calculated
    using GaussianO9.



MgO clusters
    Minimal energy structures are taken from Farrow et al. 2014
    (doi:10.1039/C4CP01825G)
    Computations with Gaussian09 were done by David Gobrecht.
    Options that were used:
    #p b3lyp/6-311+G* 5D opt=(GDIIS) integral(grid=fine) freq=noraman # GF
    INPUT # GFOLDPRINT # POP=FULL
    Tables of Gibbs free energy of formation were made by Jels Boulangier.
    (Boulangier et al in prep.)

SiO clusters
    Minimal energy structures are taken from Bromley et al. 2016
    (doi: 10.1039/c6cp03629e)
    Computations with Gaussian09 were done by David Gobrecht.
    #p b3lyp/6-311+G* 5D opt=(GDIIS) integral(grid=fine) freq=noraman # GF
    INPUT # GFOLDPRINT # POP=FULL
    Tables of Gibbs free energy of formation were made by Jels Boulangier.
    (Boulangier et al in prep.)

Al2O3 clusters
    Minimal energy structures are taken from Li, R. & Cheng, L. 2012
    (doi: 10.1016/J.COMPTC.2012.07.027)
    #p b3lyp/6-311+G* 5D opt=(GDIIS) integral(grid=fine) freq=noraman # GF
    INPUT # GFOLDPRINT # POP=FULL
    Tables of Gibbs free energy of formation were made by Jels Boulangier.
    (Boulangier et al in prep.)

Potential energy (Hartree):
    Mg: -200.0932631910 - Gaussian09 by David Gobrecht
    O: -75.0898794536   - Gaussian09 by David Gobrecht
    Si: -289.3941685040 - Gaussian09 by David Gobrecht
    Al: -242.3863975360 - Gaussian09 by David Gobrecht
